EVENTS; Lists all events in current database Show Event Details SHOW CREATE EVENT event_name; Displays full event definition Alter Event ALTER EVENT event_name ON SCHEDULE ...; Modify schedule or behavior Enable Event ALTER EVENT event_name ENABLE; Activates a disabled event Disable Event ALTER EVENT event_name DISABLE; Stops event from running Drop Event DROP EVENT event_name; Permanently deletes event Run Event Manually (Not directly possible) Must modify schedule to run immediately Lab Tasks : Use the Northwind Database Task 1 You are working as a database developer for a trading company that uses the Northwind database. Management wants a reusable procedure that generates a summary of orders for a specific customer. Create a stored procedure that: 1. Accepts a CustomerID as an input parameter. 2. Displays the following information: o Customer ID o Company Name o Total number of orders placed by the customer o Total amount spent by the customer Task 2 The management wants the system to automatically update product stock whenever a new order is placed. -- 5 of 6 -- Currently, stock quantities are stored in the Products table, but they are not updated when orders are inserted. Create a trigger that: 1. Fires AFTER INSERT on the Order Details table. 2. Automatically reduces the UnitsInStock in the Products table. 3. The reduction should be based on the ordered quantity. 4. If the stock becomes negative, prevent the operation and show an error. Task 3 The Orders table is growing rapidly, which affects performance. Management wants old orders to be archived automatically. To allow testing in the lab, the event should run every 10 seconds instead of daily. Create a MySQL Event that: 1. Runs automatically every 10 seconds. 2. Moves orders older than 5 years from the Orders table to a new table called Orders_Archive. 3. Deletes the moved records from the Orders table. 4. Ensures no duplicate records are inserted into the archive. 5. Allows students to verify execution im